<body>
  <h1>Zavod INTUS – Metacognitive Epistemic Lab</h1>
  <p class="tagline">
    INTUS is an experimental architecture for contradiction-aware, ontology-grounded reasoning.
  </p>

  <h2>What is INTUS?</h2>
  <p>
    INTUS is a modular epistemic engine that detects contradictions, grounds concepts in an ontology,
    clusters semantic attractors, and builds justification graphs over hypotheses and evidence.
  </p>

  <h2>Synthetic World Demo</h2>
  <p>
    The current prototype runs on a controlled micro-world, demonstrating:
    contradiction detection, ontology grounding, concept clustering, and justification-graph formation.
  </p>

  <h2>Zavod INTUS</h2>
  <p>
    Zavod INTUS is a metacognition lab based in Slovenia, focusing on epistemic AI, cognitive architectures,
    and symbolic–statistical hybrid reasoning systems.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Email: <a href="mailto:lab@intusmetacognition.org">lab@intusmetacognition.org</a>
  </p>
